item.title: Happy Birthday Tico!
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

[quote=“the elve age, post:28, topic:365275”][quote author=Tico link=topic=461478.msg3376277#msg3376277 date=1287626607]

Can you finally drive now? If you lived in the US you could. Congratulations!

Ahaha, well I’m not quite sure how it works in the US, but up here we have a written “G1” test (which can be taken at 16), whereas if you pass you can drive, but there has to be someone who has 4+ years of driving experience in the front seat, and you can’t drive on the highways. After 12 months, or 8 months with driving school, you can get your “G2” which means you can drive by yourself, but you still have limitations such as blood alcohol level, number of people you can have in the car, etc. 6 months after that, you may take the “G” test which has no restrictions, but is the hardest test of them all. But anyway, I got my G1 today during my lunch hour, so it’s better than nothing. But thanks.
[/quote]Are they all written exams? No actual driving test?

Only the G1 is a written test. The G2 and G tests are both in car driving tests.

Where do you live? (Related to the types of tests, which are not in US)[/quote]Look at his profile?

Personal Text: Canadian
Location: Canada
